WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:02.803
My name is Michael Westen.

00:02.870 --> 00:05.573
I used to be a spy until--

00:05.639 --> 00:07.975
- [ Man ] We got a burn notice
on you. You're blacklisted.
- [ Whistles ]

00:08.042 --> 00:10.444
[ Michael Narrating ]
When you're burned,
you've got nothing--

00:10.511 --> 00:13.247
no cash, no credit,
no job history.

00:13.314 --> 00:15.616
You're stuck in whatever city
they decide to dump you in.

00:15.683 --> 00:17.218
- Where am I?
- Miami.

00:18.152 --> 00:20.788
You do whatever work
comes your way.

00:20.854 --> 00:24.125
- You rely on anyone
who's still talking to you--
- [ Laughs ]

00:24.192 --> 00:26.494
- a trigger-happy
ex-girlfriend--
- Should we shoot them?

00:26.560 --> 00:29.330
an old friend
who used to inform on you
to the F.B.I.--

00:29.397 --> 00:31.632
You know spies.
Bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:31.699 --> 00:34.068
- Family too--
- Hey, is that your mom again?

00:34.135 --> 00:36.437
- if you're desperate.
- Someone needs
your help, Michael.

00:36.504 --> 00:40.374
Bottom line:
As long as you're burned,
you're not going anywhere.

00:48.849 --> 00:50.651
[ Michael Narrating ]
In the intelligence community,

00:50.718 --> 00:53.654
the enemy is less likely to hide
behind Kevlar and camouflage...

00:53.721 --> 00:57.158
than offshore accounts
and blind trusts.

00:58.759 --> 01:01.162
Once you pick up a bad guy's
money trail, though,

01:01.229 --> 01:03.464
finding them is just a matter
of doing your homework.

01:05.266 --> 01:09.237
If you can find
where they spend their cash,
you know where they are.

01:11.105 --> 01:15.143
If you can find where they got
their cash, you can figure out
where they came from.

01:15.943 --> 01:17.478
[ Camera Shutter Clicking ]

01:19.113 --> 01:23.551
Ravel Stigler--
unofficial banker
to cold-war leftovers,

01:23.617 --> 01:25.586
including our mystery man,
Tavian Korzha.

01:25.653 --> 01:28.122
So we know who Max's killer
got his money from. What now?

01:28.189 --> 01:29.457
Yeah, "what now"
is the problem.

01:29.523 --> 01:31.359
Stigler's
got a nasty reputation.

01:31.425 --> 01:34.262
Runs with heavy security.
Talking to him's gonna be a lot
harder than finding him was.

01:34.328 --> 01:35.896
And finding him
was very hard.

01:35.963 --> 01:37.865
I'm being framed
for murder, Sam.

01:37.931 --> 01:40.534
He may be my only link
to the real killer.
I'll take my chances.

01:42.203 --> 01:43.604
Uh, yeah, Mike, maybe not.

01:43.671 --> 01:46.106
I mean, the C.I.A. investigation
is getting pretty close.

01:46.174 --> 01:48.942
I think your best bet
is to cozy up with Pearce
and see what she knows.

01:49.009 --> 01:51.645
Sam's right.
We'll run point on Stigler.
We just need an approach.

01:53.581 --> 01:55.082
Well, this might help.
[ Shuffling Papers ]

01:55.149 --> 01:57.451
I found some messages
between Tavian
and his moneylender.

01:57.518 --> 02:01.722
Sounds like Stigler thought
he was financing an import
business, not a killing spree.

02:01.789 --> 02:04.758
So Tavian lied to him.
You think that's enough
to bond with the guy?

02:04.825 --> 02:06.360
It'll have to be.

02:19.273 --> 02:21.509
Hey.
Want a beer?

02:21.575 --> 02:24.445
No, I prefer to be sober
when I'm risking my life.
Thanks.

02:24.512 --> 02:26.580
Is Stigler here?
Private party in the back.

02:29.016 --> 02:32.420
He's got a lot of friends here.
We got about a minute of
alone time when this goes down.

02:32.486 --> 02:35.155
All right. Well,
we better talk fast then.

02:40.761 --> 02:42.796
Hey, bathroom's
that way, right?
[ Indistinct ]

02:45.266 --> 02:46.767
[ Glass Shatters ]

02:47.735 --> 02:49.337
[ Jesse ]
Hello.
[ Woman ] Oh!

02:51.405 --> 02:53.274
You break into
my place like this?

02:53.341 --> 02:55.376
Are you insane,
or you want to die?

02:57.911 --> 03:00.581
Uh, neither.
We just need a minute
of your time.

03:00.648 --> 03:02.616
[ Banging On Door ]
You have as long as it takes...

03:02.683 --> 03:06.086
for my men
to break down that door
and shoot you in the head.

03:06.153 --> 03:09.390
Then we'll get right
to the point. You loaned money
to a man named Tavian, correct?

03:09.457 --> 03:11.892
[ Banging Continues ]
[ Chuckles ]
Tavian--

03:11.959 --> 03:15.229
In my country,
this is popular name,
like Bob.

03:15.296 --> 03:17.197
We'll take that
as a yes.
[ Men Shouting ]

03:17.265 --> 03:18.632
You know what he did
with that money?

03:18.699 --> 03:20.601
He used it to kill
a C.I.A. officer.

03:22.336 --> 03:25.005
I am businessman.
This does not concern me.

03:25.072 --> 03:27.308
No?
Maybe that does.

03:27.375 --> 03:29.209
[ Banging Continues ]

03:30.010 --> 03:31.279
Lucien.

03:31.345 --> 03:34.515
He is a friend.
What do you know of him?

03:34.582 --> 03:37.017
- We know he's dead.
- You lie.

03:37.084 --> 03:40.754
Check for yourself.
Tavian used the money
to buy an HK91.

03:40.821 --> 03:42.456
Then he used that gun
to murder Lucien.

03:42.523 --> 03:44.458
- How do you know this?
- I was there.

03:45.693 --> 03:47.461
- [ Weapons Cocking ]
- [ Speaking Romanian ]

03:49.730 --> 03:53.367
I'll ask around.
Hope for your sake
you're telling the truth.

03:54.067 --> 03:55.636
Your life depends on it.

03:55.703 --> 03:58.806
Trust me, buddy.
We got a few lives
riding on this one.

04:10.384 --> 04:12.586
[ Michael Narrating ]
Solving the murder
of a covert operative...

04:12.653 --> 04:15.289
is a little different than
most homicide investigations.

04:15.356 --> 04:19.860
The pool of suspects is smaller,
but so are the odds that
the killer got sloppy.

04:19.927 --> 04:22.763
When leads are more precious
and motives more plentiful,

04:22.830 --> 04:25.065
you have to look at the case
from every angle,

04:25.132 --> 04:28.035
because you never know
where you'll find the killer.

04:28.101 --> 04:29.403
Agent Pearce.
How is it going?

04:29.470 --> 04:32.406
The Romanian connection
looked so promising.

04:32.473 --> 04:35.409
But so far, nothing.

04:35.476 --> 04:37.378
Then take me off the bench.
I'd like to.

04:37.445 --> 04:38.812
But Langley
was so
impressed...

04:38.879 --> 04:40.414
with your work
in our last
extraction,

04:40.481 --> 04:42.550
they've made
you their go-to
bad guy grabber.

04:42.616 --> 04:46.253
So where am
I heading to now?
Puerto la Cruz.

04:46.320 --> 04:50.324
Beach town outside Caracas.
We intercepted
some Russian chatter.

04:50.391 --> 04:53.226
Seems one of their assets
is taking a little vacation
there with his wife.

04:53.293 --> 04:54.428
This asset have a name?

04:54.495 --> 04:56.464
They refer to him
only as "Cheshire."

04:56.530 --> 05:00.368
He creates the nasty bugs
used in germ warfare
for the Eastern Bloc.

05:00.434 --> 05:02.069
But other than that,
we don't know much.

05:02.135 --> 05:05.038
You want me to bring him back so
you can get to know him better.
His wife too.

05:05.105 --> 05:06.674
She might know something.

05:06.740 --> 05:08.676
I'm an equal-opportunity
extractor.

05:08.742 --> 05:11.011
Speaking of wives,
this job calls for...

05:11.078 --> 05:12.846
Brendan and Christina Jenson.

05:12.913 --> 05:15.683
It's a couples resort.
I was supposed to be Christina,

05:15.749 --> 05:18.586
but I don't want to lose my
head of steam with Max's case.

05:18.652 --> 05:20.521
So I got tickets
for you and Ms. Glenanne.

05:21.955 --> 05:23.657
The agency approved Fi.

05:23.724 --> 05:27.194
As you know, relations
with Venezuela are sensitive.

05:27.260 --> 05:30.063
If things go wrong, it's easy
for the C.I.A. to disavow--

05:30.130 --> 05:33.166
burned spy and his arms-dealer
girlfriend tried to get chummy
with a mad scientist.

05:33.233 --> 05:35.035
Good to know
Langley has our backs.

05:35.102 --> 05:37.471
Go. Have fun.

05:37.538 --> 05:39.907
Bring me back a souvenir or two.

05:39.973 --> 05:41.575
Preferably in cuffs.

05:43.110 --> 05:46.146
I like a good extraction
as much as the next girl.

05:46.213 --> 05:49.683
But when I asked
for quality time,
I didn't mean on a job.

05:52.052 --> 05:55.623
Don't think of it as a job.
Think of it as
a romantic getaway, Fi.

05:56.490 --> 05:57.858
A romantic getaway.

05:57.925 --> 05:59.860
Tracking
a biological weapons engineer.

05:59.927 --> 06:02.563
The resort has
a full-service spa...

06:02.630 --> 06:05.466
and a four-star restaurant
with Chef--

06:07.234 --> 06:08.802
Louis. Luis.

06:10.438 --> 06:13.407
As much as I would enjoy a meal
that doesn't come out
of a yogurt cup,

06:13.474 --> 06:15.175
it's not about
fancy trips for me.

06:15.242 --> 06:17.978
It's about... connecting.

06:19.246 --> 06:21.715
I thought we were connecting
just fine last night.

06:22.750 --> 06:24.084
You know that's not what I mean.

06:24.151 --> 06:26.820
I know, but sometimes
it's really hard to
read your mind.

06:26.887 --> 06:28.422
[ Sighs ]

06:29.790 --> 06:33.694
How is it, when you are dealing
with drug lords or mob bosses,

06:33.761 --> 06:36.363
you know exactly what to say and
do, but when it comes to me--

06:36.430 --> 06:38.466
I'm trying, Fi.

06:38.532 --> 06:40.400
I mean, I thought
this would be a good start.

06:40.468 --> 06:43.571
It's not ideal,
but we'd be together.

06:43.637 --> 06:47.508
And vacationing on the C.I.A.'s
dime is not all that bad.

06:47.575 --> 06:50.544
Look. We've got
a discretionary fund.

06:53.080 --> 06:55.783
I'll add
a new dress to
my collection.

06:56.484 --> 06:57.651
And some shoes.

07:00.220 --> 07:02.856
Here you go, Consuelo.
It's all yours.
Thanks.

07:02.923 --> 07:04.492
So you think Stigler's
gonna show?

07:04.558 --> 07:07.695
Well, we crashed his party
and asked him to give up
one of his customers.

07:07.761 --> 07:10.130
Whether it's to help us
or kill us, he'll show.

07:10.197 --> 07:11.565
Oh, here we go.

07:13.934 --> 07:14.702
Hey, fellas.

07:16.003 --> 07:17.538
How's the thumb?

07:17.605 --> 07:19.507
Checked with my guys.

07:19.573 --> 07:21.842
Seems what you say
about Tavian is true.

07:21.909 --> 07:23.143
Hey, would I steer you wrong?

07:24.478 --> 07:27.481
He comes Tuesday, 2:00.

07:27.548 --> 07:29.249
He parks here
in alley.

07:29.316 --> 07:33.453
He comes in, takes money,
goes back to car and leaves--

07:33.521 --> 07:35.155
In and out,
maybe a minute.

07:35.222 --> 07:36.624
That's long enough
to grab him.

07:36.690 --> 07:39.326
Tavian is a dangerous man.

07:39.392 --> 07:43.063
If you fail,
it will be bad.

07:43.130 --> 07:44.131
You understand?

07:44.197 --> 07:46.133
Believe me, we understand.

07:48.936 --> 07:50.571
Okay. So Mike and Fi
get to kick back...

07:50.638 --> 07:52.139
and sip mojitos in the sun,

07:52.205 --> 07:54.942
and we get to set a bear trap
for an international killer.

07:55.008 --> 07:55.943
Sweet.

08:09.990 --> 08:11.725
[ Michael Narrating ]
Working a cover
at a foreign resort...

08:11.792 --> 08:13.527
isn't about
keeping a low profile.

08:13.594 --> 08:15.863
It's about having as
much access as possible.

08:15.929 --> 08:18.431
Arrive in a nice car
and tip extravagantly,

08:18.498 --> 08:21.268
and the service staff will open
all sorts of doors for you.

08:21.334 --> 08:24.071
If you want to rub elbows
with the other guests,

08:24.137 --> 08:26.306
select a cover that gives you
an excuse to be social...

08:26.373 --> 08:29.643
and a reason for the hotel to
upgrade you to a central room.

08:29.710 --> 08:31.779
Travel writer
usually works fine.

08:31.845 --> 08:34.181
We have a lovely suite for you.

08:34.247 --> 08:36.149
- Please enjoy your stay.
- [ Fiona ]
Thank you.

08:36.216 --> 08:39.352
It's a good idea to make use
of all the hotel's amenities.

08:39.419 --> 08:41.121
A laptop and
some hacking software...

08:41.188 --> 08:43.791
can get you access to
the hotel's database...

08:44.892 --> 08:47.728
and give you free pay-per-view
in the process.

08:49.496 --> 08:51.464
How does
the discretionary fund look?

08:51.531 --> 08:53.166
Expensive.

08:53.233 --> 08:56.336
Four couples' check-in dates
match Cheshire's.

08:56.403 --> 08:58.138
[ Fiona ]
So one of these guys
is our germ maker.

08:58.205 --> 09:00.140
Tonight's the perfect time
to check 'em out.

09:01.308 --> 09:03.877
Aren't you
forgetting something?
No, no.

09:03.944 --> 09:05.946
I downloaded
their room numbers
onto my phone.

09:06.013 --> 09:10.550
We're Mr. and Mrs. Jenson,
are we not?
Yeah. Oh.

09:12.853 --> 09:14.622
Aren't you gonna
get down on bended knee?

09:22.630 --> 09:24.131
We got work to do.

09:25.933 --> 09:27.500
It's an ugly rock,
anyway.

09:27.567 --> 09:30.671
** [ Waltz ]

09:34.241 --> 09:35.475
Well, I'll give you this.

09:35.542 --> 09:38.345
This is the nicest place
you've ever taken me
for surveillance.

09:38.411 --> 09:40.814
All of our Cheshires
are here.

09:40.881 --> 09:42.816
From the looks of it,
so is the rest of the resort.

09:42.883 --> 09:45.185
Thank God these heels
have arch support.

09:45.252 --> 09:47.320
** [ Samba ]

09:47.387 --> 09:48.889
Shall we?

09:48.956 --> 09:50.624
I thought you'd never ask.

09:50.691 --> 09:52.425
[ Michael Narrating ]
When gathering intelligence,

09:52.492 --> 09:57.297
operatives often rely on
binoculars, hidden cameras and
electronic listening devices.

09:57.364 --> 10:02.569
But sometimes all it takes
is a well-dressed date
and a decent sense of rhythm.

10:02.636 --> 10:06.774
If you're light on your feet,
you can study a crowd
without standing out in it...

10:06.840 --> 10:09.576
and examine every angle
of a room with a simple spin.

10:09.643 --> 10:13.380
The first step, of course,
is identifying
your surveillance targets,

10:13.446 --> 10:15.182
locating them, assessing them...

10:15.248 --> 10:18.051
and coming up
with a strategy for further
intelligence gathering.

10:18.118 --> 10:21.021
The worst thing you can do
at this point is rush things.

10:21.088 --> 10:23.657
Your goal is to blend in,
plan your moves...

10:23.724 --> 10:25.292
and let the dance carry you
where you need to go.

10:25.358 --> 10:28.962
[ Woman ]
* Perhaps, perhaps, perhaps **

10:31.198 --> 10:33.901
** [ Tango ]

10:34.835 --> 10:36.870
Shall we tango?
Let's.

10:41.942 --> 10:45.378
- Can I lead?
- Fine. Just this once.

10:45.445 --> 10:48.716
The simplest kind of
surveillance, of course,
is eavesdropping--

10:48.782 --> 10:50.718
easy enough
on the dance floor,

10:50.784 --> 10:53.586
where getting close to people
is simply a matter
of knowing the right moves...

10:53.653 --> 10:55.422
and using them
at the right time.

10:55.488 --> 10:57.590
He better make me
first chair.
I've earned it.

10:57.657 --> 11:01.094
[ Sighs ]
Oh, he's the bad guy,
but just the lawyer kind.

11:03.697 --> 11:05.799
More-direct approaches
can work as well.

11:05.866 --> 11:07.901
Dancing alongside someone
for an evening...

11:07.968 --> 11:10.904
can give you a perfect excuse
to strike up a conversation...

11:10.971 --> 11:13.206
and find out
what you need to know.

11:13.273 --> 11:15.342
You and your husband
make such a cute couple.

11:15.408 --> 11:17.978
Oh. We're not married... yet.

11:20.714 --> 11:21.849
They're not married.

11:24.651 --> 11:28.155
You can even pull off
a covert weapons check,
if you're careful.

11:28.221 --> 11:31.091
Under his jacket--
could be a gun.

11:32.059 --> 11:32.960
Spin me.

11:34.361 --> 11:36.163
Ooh. Excuse me.

11:37.630 --> 11:38.832
Smartphone.

11:50.610 --> 11:52.412
Doesn't mean he's not our guy.

11:57.417 --> 12:00.788
** [ Classical ]
It has to be
Serge and Karina.

12:00.854 --> 12:04.224
They don't dance, they've barely
touched their drinks
and they keep eyeing the door.

12:04.291 --> 12:08.095
Well, unless Serge
is a child prodigy,

12:08.161 --> 12:10.898
he's way too young
to be a bioweapons guy.

12:10.964 --> 12:13.767
You have a better prospect?
Hmm.

12:13.834 --> 12:16.569
It's those two.
They're using
a fake name.

12:16.636 --> 12:18.071
Oh? And how do you
know that?

12:18.138 --> 12:19.873
They're listed as
Kevin and Nicki Skylar,

12:19.940 --> 12:24.477
but when the waiter called him
"Mr. Skylar," it took him
a good two seconds to react.

12:24.544 --> 12:27.214
Well, maybe
he was preoccupied.
[ Beeping ]

12:27.280 --> 12:29.983
You know men--
so easily distracted.

12:31.118 --> 12:33.720
Hmm? Yeah,
one way to find out--

12:33.787 --> 12:35.122
They're staying
in Room 441.

12:35.188 --> 12:38.491
We should go
before they finish dinner.

12:38.558 --> 12:40.760
We don't get to
finish our wine?

12:40.828 --> 12:42.830
It's a Kosta Browne.

12:53.140 --> 12:54.541
Work fast.
I'll keep watch.

12:54.607 --> 12:56.977
[ Michael Narrating ]
An outlet is the ideal place...

12:57.044 --> 12:58.645
to plant a bug in a hotel.

12:58.711 --> 13:00.647
Not only do they provide power,

13:00.713 --> 13:03.917
but any audio picked up
can be transmitted
through the wires...

13:03.984 --> 13:05.785
to any other outlet
in the building,

13:05.853 --> 13:09.722
as long as you can manage
to hook into a live circuit
without electrocuting yourself.

13:09.789 --> 13:12.625
Hurry, Michael. The Skylars
are calling it an early night.

13:12.692 --> 13:13.827
Thirty seconds.

13:19.967 --> 13:22.669
More bad news.
We were both right.

13:22.735 --> 13:24.905
Mr. Skylar
is the death merchant.

13:28.075 --> 13:29.943
My couple-- bodyguards.

13:37.617 --> 13:40.420
- Let's go.
- Not this way.
It's too late.

13:45.658 --> 13:47.427
[ Indistinct ]

13:47.494 --> 13:49.963
[ Michael Narrating ]
As a spy, improvising to get
out of tough situations...

13:50.030 --> 13:52.799
is just part of the job.

13:52.866 --> 13:57.337
Sometimes that means
stealing a car
to get away from a gun battle.

13:57.404 --> 14:00.407
- We gonna have
any privacy, ever?
- They have to check the room.

14:00.473 --> 14:03.877
Other times, it means destroying
a $2,000 dress...

14:03.944 --> 14:05.712
to climb down safely
from a hotel balcony.

14:05.778 --> 14:07.380
[ Both Mouthing Words ]

14:08.882 --> 14:09.883
[ Fabric Tears ]

14:20.393 --> 14:23.130
You do what you have to do
to survive,

14:23.196 --> 14:26.633
but it doesn't mean
you won't upset someone
in the process.

14:26.699 --> 14:29.136
You always know
how to show a girl
a good time, Michael.

14:36.543 --> 14:38.211
[ Kevin Over Speaker ]
Will you just--

14:38.278 --> 14:40.380
Will you please put away that
bottle and calm down, Nicki?

14:40.447 --> 14:42.649
You're being irrational.
I don't even know
what you're saying.

14:42.715 --> 14:47.320
I am saying that
this trip is so lame,
I could scream!

14:47.387 --> 14:49.056
[ Kevin ]
Will you keep
your voice down?

14:49.122 --> 14:51.591
Are you really gonna
listen to this all night?

14:51.658 --> 14:55.628
There's trouble in paradise.
I think you get the gist.

14:55.695 --> 14:57.097
The more we know about them,

14:57.164 --> 15:00.133
the easier it will be
to get them to the helipad
for the extraction, Fi.

15:00.200 --> 15:01.935
[ Nicki ]
...get a manicure!
[ Kevin ] You're drunk.

15:02.002 --> 15:03.136
I think we know plenty.

15:04.237 --> 15:08.241
That they're American,
traitors, married.

15:08.308 --> 15:10.443
Apparently,
they hate each other.

15:10.510 --> 15:14.214
You think that
I just wish your Prada bags
into existence, Nicki?

15:14.281 --> 15:15.782
I have to
work for them.

15:15.848 --> 15:17.884
[ Nicki Scoffs ]
What the hell
do you want from me?

15:17.951 --> 15:22.122
I want to go on a vacation
where I don't have Russian goons
telling me where to go...

15:22.189 --> 15:24.724
or what time
I have to go to bed!

15:24.791 --> 15:26.960
I want a real life!
God!

15:27.027 --> 15:28.328
[ Door Slams ]

15:29.997 --> 15:31.764
I guess selling
bioweapons secrets...

15:31.831 --> 15:33.733
wasn't quite the opportunity
they thought it would be.

15:33.800 --> 15:37.004
It sounds like Nicki
is desperate
for some social contact...

15:37.070 --> 15:38.538
and a little taste
of the good life.

15:38.605 --> 15:40.473
How would you feel about
making a new friend tomorrow?

15:40.540 --> 15:43.610
Why not?
[ Sighs ]

15:43.676 --> 15:45.512
We have a lot
in common.

15:45.578 --> 15:49.616
We both have
good taste in handbags,
work-obsessed men.

15:49.682 --> 15:52.219
At least I don't sell W.M.D.'s
to dictators.

15:54.721 --> 15:57.590
I'm, uh--
I'm drawing a bath.

15:59.226 --> 16:01.094
There's room for two.

16:04.564 --> 16:06.199
I would love to,

16:06.266 --> 16:08.001
but I have to type up
these notes.

16:08.601 --> 16:09.569
Okay.

16:22.815 --> 16:25.985
[ Michael Narrating ]
For a spy, making an approach
is about problem solving.

16:26.053 --> 16:29.322
I can't, okay?
Whether it's a bad marriage
or an unsatisfying job,

16:29.389 --> 16:31.558
you look for the problem,
the issue on the target's mind.

16:46.106 --> 16:48.208
Can I get you something,
Mr. Jenson?

16:48.275 --> 16:50.610
Yes. I'm hitting
the golf course,

16:50.677 --> 16:53.746
but my wife would like
a little champagne
and caviar.

16:53.813 --> 16:57.417
It's our anniversary, so make it
the good stuff, will you?
Of course, seÃ±or.

16:57.484 --> 17:01.654
Once you know the problem,
it's just a matter of turning
yourself into the solution--

17:01.721 --> 17:02.822
I'll just need your signature.

17:02.889 --> 17:04.557
and arranging a meeting.

17:11.764 --> 17:13.733
Champagne and beluga caviar.

17:15.602 --> 17:18.105
Oh, no. I'm sorry.
I didn't order this.

17:18.171 --> 17:21.341
- From your husband.
- [ Scoffs ]
I wish!

17:21.408 --> 17:22.909
My husband
isn't that splurgy.

17:22.975 --> 17:25.778
Oh. I-I'm sorry.
I think that might
actually be mine.

17:25.845 --> 17:27.714
I'm so sorry.
Here.

17:29.516 --> 17:30.983
Yum.

17:31.050 --> 17:32.952
About a thousand dollars'
worth of yum.

17:33.019 --> 17:36.556
My husband and I only
do this about once a month,
so we try to make it count.

17:38.758 --> 17:42.329
You know, my hubby is busy.
Why don't you join me?

17:43.663 --> 17:45.298
Mmm. I shouldn't.

17:45.365 --> 17:48.101
There are no shouldn'ts
on vacation.

17:49.236 --> 17:51.070
Okay.
Yeah, hit me.

17:51.138 --> 17:53.240
Hitting.
[ Giggles ]

17:56.209 --> 17:58.145
Thank you.
I'm Christina.

17:58.211 --> 18:00.480
Nicki.
Nice to meet you.

18:02.482 --> 18:04.784
Mmm.
Where's your husband?

18:04.851 --> 18:08.921
He is, uh,
probably on the phone
somewhere, as usual.

18:08.988 --> 18:10.623
[ Chuckles ]
Mine's the same way.

18:10.690 --> 18:14.661
Actually,
Brendan is being
a good boy today.

18:14.727 --> 18:17.497
He's arranging
a helicopter ride
for us.

18:17.564 --> 18:19.732
Apparently,
it's the best way to
see the rain forest.

18:21.401 --> 18:23.570
Of course,
he's only doing it
because I twisted his arm.

18:25.138 --> 18:27.874
Here's to...
being the better half.

18:27.940 --> 18:29.409
I'll drink to that.

18:31.211 --> 18:32.779
[ Sighs ]

18:35.081 --> 18:36.516
There he is. Kevin!

18:37.817 --> 18:41.388
[ Laughs ]
This is Christina.
Yeah, we met at the pool.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.556
- [ Kevin ]
Oh, nice to meet you.
- Champagne?

18:43.623 --> 18:47.460
- No, thank you.
- That's my husband-- buzzkill.

18:47.527 --> 18:49.296
[ Giggles ]
I take it this isn't
your first bottle, Nicki.

18:49.362 --> 18:51.431
Christina?
Making new friends?

18:51.498 --> 18:53.600
Mmm. Honey, this is Nicki.

18:53.666 --> 18:55.902
- Oh, and you must be Brendan.
- Yes.

18:55.968 --> 18:58.271
You never said
how handsome he is.

18:58.338 --> 19:00.106
- Brendan.
- Kevin.

19:00.173 --> 19:02.909
Darling, did you book
the helicopter tour?

19:02.975 --> 19:06.012
I tried to get something cozy,
but all they had
was a six-seater.

19:06.078 --> 19:08.315
Oh. That seems
like such a waste.

19:08.381 --> 19:09.782
I know!
Why don't you join us?

19:09.849 --> 19:11.618
There's plenty of room,
and we would love the company.

19:11.684 --> 19:15.422
That would be so fun.
[ Chuckles ]

19:17.757 --> 19:20.960
Oh, that's
incredibly generous,
but, uh, we can't.

19:21.027 --> 19:23.095
I'm sorry.
Seriously, Kevin.

19:23.162 --> 19:24.531
Look, don't decide now.

19:24.597 --> 19:26.333
Let's all grab dinner
and discuss it then.

19:26.399 --> 19:27.934
What do you say?

19:30.036 --> 19:31.238
We'll think about it.

19:31.304 --> 19:33.105
Oh. Well, hopefully,
we'll see you later?

19:33.172 --> 19:34.274
[ Giggling ]

19:37.344 --> 19:38.645
I don't think
they're going for it.

19:38.711 --> 19:40.313
They're going for it.
I know what she's thinking.

19:40.380 --> 19:42.148
I know that look
she gave him.
I'm not so sure--

19:42.215 --> 19:43.850
Christina!
We're in.

19:43.916 --> 19:46.953
Since you guys got
the helicopter tour,
dinner's on us.

19:47.019 --> 19:48.388
See you at 7:00!
7:00.

19:48.455 --> 19:50.523
[ Chuckles ]
Told ya.

19:59.899 --> 20:02.235
According to
my napkin,

20:02.302 --> 20:05.605
Tavian should pull up...
right, like, here-ish.

20:06.573 --> 20:08.508
Then he goes
into the back of the bar,

20:08.575 --> 20:10.943
gets the money,
comes back out here,
goes this way.

20:11.010 --> 20:12.379
Yup.

20:12.445 --> 20:15.448
I think we can stop him
right around that ketchup stain.

20:15.515 --> 20:16.916
You talking about
that grate right there?

20:16.983 --> 20:19.819
I'm talking about that grate
right there.
All right, cool.

20:19.886 --> 20:22.289
I got everything we need
in the back of Fi's car.
Yeah, about that--

20:22.355 --> 20:25.492
- Are you sure that Fi is cool
with us borrowing her wheels?
- She's gonna have to be.

20:25.558 --> 20:27.794
- The Porsche
is getting a tune-up.
- Okay, let's do it.

20:29.829 --> 20:31.598
[ Michael Narrating ]
Pinning down a moving target...

20:31.664 --> 20:33.800
is all about
preparation and timing.

20:33.866 --> 20:37.136
If your target will be driving,
the first task
is to stop the vehicle.

20:37.203 --> 20:39.939
If you have room,
a bigger vehicle
will do the trick.

20:40.006 --> 20:42.342
But if space is tight,
you have to improvise.

20:45.878 --> 20:48.415
Finally, if you know where
the target vehicle is headed,

20:48.481 --> 20:51.618
a directional blast
that can launch a projectile...

20:51.684 --> 20:55.488
into the engine of a car
at high speed
will stop it in its tracks.

20:55.555 --> 20:58.024
You just have to find
a place to plant it and wait.

21:00.493 --> 21:02.795
That ought to do it.
Let's go eat.
Dinner's on me.

21:02.862 --> 21:04.464
Right.

21:04.531 --> 21:07.099
Stunning views,
booze on board.

21:07.166 --> 21:08.468
You're gonna love
this chopper ride.

21:12.505 --> 21:15.274
What's wrong, Nicki?
You barely touched
your mousse.

21:15.342 --> 21:16.776
I didn't want to ruin our meal.

21:16.843 --> 21:20.913
It's just that...
my husband said that
we can't go on the tour.

21:20.980 --> 21:23.015
What? Why?

21:23.082 --> 21:24.016
Ask him.

21:27.354 --> 21:29.489
Um, I'm afraid
we don't have time.

21:29.556 --> 21:31.591
Of course you have time.
It's just a day ride.

21:31.658 --> 21:32.859
I said
I don't have time.

21:33.626 --> 21:35.595
Kevin, you're being rude.

21:35.662 --> 21:37.764
Sorry,
I just have work.

21:37.830 --> 21:40.066
My bosses need us
to be home tomorrow night.

21:40.132 --> 21:43.269
[ Michael Narrating ]
As a spy, you're trained
never to pitch assets...

21:43.336 --> 21:45.405
in situations
you don't control.

21:45.472 --> 21:47.139
Still, you can't
always avoid it.

21:47.206 --> 21:50.710
If it's a choice between that
or losing the asset altogether,

21:50.777 --> 21:53.212
sometimes you have to
grit your teeth
and roll the dice.

21:53.279 --> 21:55.582
Let's stop
with the charade, Kevin.

21:56.449 --> 21:58.017
You and I
have a lot in common.

21:58.084 --> 22:00.820
We both work hard,
we both love our wives...

22:00.887 --> 22:02.922
and we're not
who we claim to be.

22:04.757 --> 22:05.692
Excuse me?

22:05.758 --> 22:09.529
Hear him out...
and smile and nod as you do,

22:09.596 --> 22:12.331
or we're all gonna get shot
by your bodyguards.

22:12.399 --> 22:13.866
[ Both Laugh ]

22:13.933 --> 22:15.568
I'm a broker of sorts--

22:15.635 --> 22:17.637
for people with skills to sell,
like you.

22:17.704 --> 22:20.106
I-I-I don't know
what you're saying.
Course you do.

22:20.172 --> 22:22.274
Kev, I can guess
how it all went down
actually.

22:22.341 --> 22:25.812
It's always the same drill.
You were at some
pharma conference--

22:25.878 --> 22:29.416
Probably talking
about diet drugs
or cholesterol pills--

22:29.482 --> 22:32.351
Wasting that brain of yours,
and then someone made you
a better offer.

22:32.419 --> 22:33.953
Promised you the world.

22:34.020 --> 22:36.456
And then that promise
didn't really pan out,
now did it?

22:36.523 --> 22:38.090
- How did you know that?
- Nicki.

22:38.157 --> 22:39.158
- What?
- You just--

22:39.225 --> 22:41.227
The Russians are all talk.
If you're gonna sell out,

22:41.293 --> 22:42.695
you do it
to the highest bidder.

22:42.762 --> 22:44.797
I can double what you make
right now,

22:44.864 --> 22:47.767
and I won't insult you
by pushing a babysitter on you.

22:51.938 --> 22:53.840
[ Fiona ]
Looks like those babysitters
are getting suspicious.

22:54.841 --> 22:55.608
Brendan--

22:58.845 --> 23:00.447
I can give you everything
you want,

23:00.513 --> 23:02.281
but you have to decide
right now:

23:02.348 --> 23:04.617
Do you want to go back
to the gulag...

23:04.684 --> 23:06.686
with your millions
that you'll never spend or--

23:06.753 --> 23:12.391
Or would you like to come with
us to our private helicopter,
champagne on ice?

23:15.327 --> 23:17.964
Sweetheart, say yes.

23:19.331 --> 23:20.967
- You have five seconds.
- Kevin, please?

23:24.437 --> 23:25.472
Fine. I'm in.

23:25.538 --> 23:27.907
Laugh, now,
as loud as you can.

23:31.310 --> 23:34.413
Now you see why I make him
tell all his stories
in his inside voice.

23:34.481 --> 23:36.348
- Inside voice!
- You are so bad!

23:36.415 --> 23:37.784
Mmm!
[ Fiona Chuckles ]

23:37.850 --> 23:40.953
- To new friends.
- New friends.

23:52.499 --> 23:54.467
Kevin,
you don't like
your champagne?

23:54.534 --> 23:57.537
I don't want champagne.
I don't even want to be
in this pool.

23:57.604 --> 24:00.072
That's hilarious.
[ Chuckles ]

24:00.139 --> 24:01.908
Remember,
we're supposed to
keep up appear--

24:01.974 --> 24:04.010
Appearances. I know.
You keep saying that.

24:04.076 --> 24:07.446
What you didn't say
was how any of this
was actually going to work.

24:07.514 --> 24:12.552
Well, first, you stay calm,
sip your bubbly.
Just relaxing with friends.

24:12.619 --> 24:14.787
Please. "Relax." He forgot
the meaning of that word...

24:14.854 --> 24:16.288
when he started
working for the Russians.

24:16.355 --> 24:19.458
Our chopper arrives at 4:00.
We'll all meet at the helipad--

24:19.526 --> 24:20.860
soon as we ditch
your babysitters.

24:20.927 --> 24:24.163
That's your plan?
Ditch 'em?

24:24.230 --> 24:27.033
We can't ditch 'em.
They never let us
leave their sight.

24:27.099 --> 24:30.670
Not to mention,
they're always carrying
a gun at all times.

24:30.737 --> 24:32.204
If we try to run,
they're gonna shoot us.

24:32.271 --> 24:34.173
We won't
give them the chance.
[ Chuckles ]

24:34.240 --> 24:38.711
You and I are going
to the steam room
for a little R & R.

24:38.778 --> 24:43.082
Serge won't be able to wear
his Kevlar vest or his machine
pistol on him under his towel.

24:43.149 --> 24:45.518
And we have lunch
at a trÃ¨s chic restaurant
across town.

24:45.585 --> 24:47.319
We have reservations
on the patio.

24:47.386 --> 24:50.757
Karina will be stuck at the bar,
which gives us enough room
to slip away.

24:50.823 --> 24:53.125
Are you sure?
These guys are
seriously scary.

24:53.192 --> 24:55.494
Trust me.
We'll have everything we need
to take care of them.

24:55.562 --> 24:59.131
And once we lose them
and get to the cars,
we'll have plenty of firepower.

24:59.198 --> 25:01.233
I don't know.
This seems like
an awfully big risk.

25:02.569 --> 25:04.704
With an even bigger reward
at the end of it.

25:04.771 --> 25:06.338
Just think of the life
you'll have.

25:06.405 --> 25:07.940
Anything is better
than this life.

25:08.908 --> 25:11.343
The scary part
is almost over.

25:11.410 --> 25:14.847
And soon,
we'll all be filthy rich.

25:14.914 --> 25:16.849
We should get dressed
for lunch.

25:16.916 --> 25:19.619
I'll see you
later, darling.
[ Mock Whimper ]

25:19.686 --> 25:21.621
- [ Whispers ]
Be careful.
- I'll miss you too.

25:28.661 --> 25:30.529
[ Shotgun Racks ]

25:30.597 --> 25:32.198
So who do you think's
having more fun right now:

25:32.264 --> 25:34.901
Mike and Fi in paradise,
waiting for mojito refills,

25:34.967 --> 25:38.004
or you and me in a back alley,
waiting for
a Romanian assassin?

25:38.070 --> 25:40.940
I'd be having
a lot more fun if Tavian
would show up already.

25:41.007 --> 25:43.710
Should have been here
a half hour ago.
It's hot.

25:43.776 --> 25:45.244
You think Stigler
might have tipped him off?

25:45.311 --> 25:47.747
I don't know.
I'll go ask him.

25:49.248 --> 25:52.051
You mind watching my back,
just in case Tavian's
fashionably late?

25:52.118 --> 25:54.186
As long as you bring me a beer
on the way back out.

26:02.261 --> 26:03.896
Oh, damn it.

26:08.534 --> 26:10.169
Sam, we got a problem.
Stigler's dead.

26:10.236 --> 26:11.237
[ Hammer Cocks ]

26:12.471 --> 26:15.141
Hands up.
Phone off. Now.

26:17.677 --> 26:19.712
Sam, can you hear me?

26:20.947 --> 26:22.348
Sam.

26:31.590 --> 26:35.127
Nice place.
You bring all your kills here,
or is this our special spot?

26:35.194 --> 26:37.697
If I wanted to kill you,
you'd be dead already.

26:37.764 --> 26:40.099
I want a meeting
with Michael Westen.

26:40.166 --> 26:43.135
- You're gonna arrange it.
- You want to meet with Mike.

26:43.202 --> 26:45.171
You killed his buddy
and framed him for murder.

26:45.237 --> 26:47.106
I don't think he's real eager
to grab a latte with you.

26:47.173 --> 26:49.075
You can tell him
about the meeting,

26:49.141 --> 26:52.611
or I can send him
a written invitation
pinned to your corpse.

26:52.679 --> 26:54.113
Let's go with option A.

26:54.180 --> 26:59.285
Tell Michael I want a truce,
and I have answers.

26:59.351 --> 27:03.155
Yeah? To what?
To questions
he doesn't even know to ask.

27:03.222 --> 27:06.358
I'm sure Mike
would be very intrigued, but
he's a little busy right now.

27:06.425 --> 27:07.760
Tell him to
clear his calendar.

27:07.827 --> 27:11.230
Tomorrow, 6:00 p.m.,
Brickell Key Park.

27:12.431 --> 27:13.966
I won't wait.

27:15.534 --> 27:17.269
[ Car Door Closes ]
[ Engine Starts ]

27:26.779 --> 27:29.248
[ Michael Narrating ]
People tend to overestimate
the value of weapons.

27:29.315 --> 27:31.517
Choosing the time
and place of a fight...

27:31.583 --> 27:34.553
is often more important
than having a lot of firepower.

27:34.620 --> 27:38.691
It doesn't matter
if all you've got is
some spa rocks and a wet towel.

27:38.758 --> 27:43.896
If you can surprise an unarmed
opponent on favorable ground,
that can be all you need.

27:43.963 --> 27:45.832
Kevin, sit down.
You're supposed to relax.

27:45.898 --> 27:47.800
You know what?
I'll be relaxed...

27:47.867 --> 27:51.704
when we're in the air
and this dump is just
a speck on the horizon.

27:51.771 --> 27:55.641
We're almost there.
All you have to do is
soak in the healing mist...

27:55.708 --> 27:58.377
and distract Serge
when he shows up.

27:58.444 --> 28:01.213
And then, once you get
your, uh-- your opening,
I can-- I can go, right?

28:01.280 --> 28:03.515
You go back
to the locker rooms.
You wait there.

28:03.582 --> 28:05.084
Just kill some time.

28:05.151 --> 28:06.652
Fantasize about
how much money
you're gonna make.

28:06.719 --> 28:08.587
About that--

28:08.654 --> 28:13.793
I have been working
on this new neurotoxin--
like nothing you have ever seen.

28:13.860 --> 28:15.995
I'm talking
total organ failure.

28:16.062 --> 28:17.463
They drop like that.
[ Snaps Fingers ]

28:17.529 --> 28:21.233
Russians weren't interested,
but North Koreans might be.

28:21.300 --> 28:23.369
We'll shop it around.
You'll get
what you deserve.

28:25.071 --> 28:27.273
- [ Clears Throat ]
- [ Door Opens ]

28:30.642 --> 28:33.846
- [ Clears Throat ]
- You should have waited for me
before coming in here.

28:33.913 --> 28:37.649
Do I need to, uh, have you
escort me to the bathroom too?
[ Chuckles ]

28:37.716 --> 28:39.986
I'm fine, Serge.
Where is your friend?

28:40.052 --> 28:42.421
How the hell should I know?
Maybe he's getting a massage.

28:42.488 --> 28:43.722
Serge.

28:45.457 --> 28:45.992
Come on.

28:49.762 --> 28:50.930
[ Groans ]

29:07.847 --> 29:09.248
[ Grunts ]

29:27.900 --> 29:29.201
Sleep tight, Serge.

29:32.138 --> 29:34.841
[ Phone Beeps ]
Hmm, seems the boys
had a cleansing sweat,

29:34.907 --> 29:36.442
rid themselves
of unwanted company.

29:36.508 --> 29:39.946
Well, then I guess
that means it's our turn.
Exactly.

29:40.012 --> 29:42.114
I picked the key
to the patio door
off the bar manager.

29:42.181 --> 29:46.518
So I'm gonna get up, lock
the door, and then we'll start
making our way out of here.

29:46.585 --> 29:50.456
Oh. Well, do you
really think a locked door
is gonna stop her?

29:50.522 --> 29:52.491
No, but it'll buy us
enough time to
get to the car.

29:52.558 --> 29:55.794
[ Sighs ]
I think I'm gonna need
a glass of wine.

29:55.862 --> 29:57.363
Maybe a bottle.

29:58.297 --> 30:00.232
All you need
is to stay calm.

30:00.299 --> 30:03.135
This only works
if Karina has no idea
what's going on.

30:03.202 --> 30:05.872
Okay.
Yeah, I can do that.

30:09.141 --> 30:10.509
Hey, Nicki.
Yeah?

30:10.576 --> 30:12.578
Keep staring at Karina
like a scared little bunny,

30:12.644 --> 30:13.980
you're gonna tip her off.

30:14.046 --> 30:15.747
Just--
[ Inhales ]

30:15.814 --> 30:17.316
take in the view,
read the menu,

30:17.383 --> 30:19.051
focus on anything
but her, okay?

30:19.118 --> 30:21.587
Okay.
I'm gonna go
to the buffet now.

30:21.653 --> 30:22.554
Okay.

30:38.304 --> 30:39.138
Oh!

30:51.951 --> 30:54.353
- What did I tell you about
those bunny eyes? Come on.
- Sorry.

30:56.388 --> 30:58.257
[ People Screaming ]
[ Woman ]
Look out!

31:00.126 --> 31:03.395
- [ Nicki Screams ]
- Come on, up and over.
In the drink, honey! Come on!

31:18.877 --> 31:20.312
We've got to get
to the car.

31:21.080 --> 31:22.881
[ Nicki Screams ]
Geez!

31:26.518 --> 31:28.955
Call for help!
My phone is at
the bottom of the bay.

31:29.021 --> 31:31.023
We're on our own.
We have to make a run for it.

31:31.090 --> 31:33.392
Okay, well, the car is
way too far from here.

31:35.727 --> 31:37.663
Well, then we'll arrange for
another mode of transportation.

31:37.729 --> 31:39.165
Keep your head down.
Follow me.

31:40.666 --> 31:42.168
Um, I don't ride.

31:43.902 --> 31:45.938
- Yeah, but you know
how to be clingy.
- [ Engine Starts ]

31:47.439 --> 31:48.640
Come on!

32:04.991 --> 32:06.558
[ Michael Narrating ]
As tactical vehicles,

32:06.625 --> 32:08.827
motorcycles have advantages
and disadvantages.

32:08.894 --> 32:13.599
Their off-the-line acceleration
leaves most four-wheel vehicles
in their dust.

32:13.665 --> 32:17.603
But as a vehicle for
bursting through a roadblock,
you can't do much worse.

32:31.883 --> 32:33.519
What are you doing?
Why are we stopping?

32:33.585 --> 32:36.655
Your babysitter must have called
all her Russian friends.

32:39.225 --> 32:40.892
We'll never make it
past that roadblock.

32:40.959 --> 32:42.861
Well, can we go back out
to the main road?

32:42.928 --> 32:44.630
Karina will
have that covered.

32:44.696 --> 32:47.299
Okay, so let's hide.
Let's go into the woods.

32:47.366 --> 32:49.468
They'll comb every inch
of those trees.

32:49.535 --> 32:51.870
It's not a question
of if they get us,
it's a question of when.

32:51.937 --> 32:53.372
We have to stay and fight.

32:53.439 --> 32:57.043
I dig the girl power,
but, uh, Karina,
she brought her friends.

32:57.109 --> 32:58.544
We're outnumbered.
They're totally gonna kill us.

32:59.678 --> 33:00.946
Probably,

33:01.013 --> 33:02.714
but I'm not a big fan
of going quietly.

33:07.319 --> 33:09.755
Where's our chopper?
It'll be here
in five minutes.

33:11.357 --> 33:14.193
Five minutes,
and we are home free.

33:14.260 --> 33:17.163
Our wives should have
been here by now.

33:17.229 --> 33:18.930
Their route was shorter
than ours.
[ Phone Beeps ]

33:18.997 --> 33:20.666
[ Sighs ]

33:22.734 --> 33:24.670
They're not answering.
Something's wrong.
[ Beeps ]

33:24.736 --> 33:27.573
Maybe they hit traffic.
If Karina
was tipped off,

33:27.639 --> 33:30.409
she would have
called in reinforcements
and cut off the roads.

33:30.476 --> 33:32.078
It's right out of
the F.S.B. playbook.

33:32.144 --> 33:34.980
We're going back
for them.
Are you insane?

33:35.047 --> 33:39.485
No, you said yourself
our chopper's gonna be here
in five minutes.

33:39.551 --> 33:41.553
- It's time to cut our losses.
- Our losses?

33:41.620 --> 33:44.123
I can see why your wife
finds you so charming.

33:44.790 --> 33:46.358
[ Tires Squealing ]

33:50.529 --> 33:52.531
Hey, help me
clean off these bullets.

33:52.598 --> 33:54.366
Least we'll stand
a fighting chance.

33:54.433 --> 33:58.204
He had a medical degree!
What girl goes wrong
marrying a doctor?

33:58.270 --> 34:01.940
If I'd known what I was
signing up for, I would
never accepted this damn ring.

34:02.007 --> 34:03.375
Know what I mean?
Not really.

34:03.442 --> 34:06.044
Mine's a fake.
Really?

34:06.112 --> 34:07.746
[ Engine Revving ]

34:10.582 --> 34:11.883
They're here.
[ Slide Cocks ]

34:11.950 --> 34:14.052
Keep those coming.
Get down.

34:20.192 --> 34:22.094
[ Speaking Russian ]

34:33.038 --> 34:34.573
- [ Groans ]
- [ Body Thuds ]

34:44.316 --> 34:47.319
Two down, one to go.
Here. That's
our last bullet.

34:48.954 --> 34:50.789
She's coming.
Get back.

34:54.526 --> 34:55.827
[ Clicks ]

34:57.329 --> 34:59.731
Ah, gun problems?

35:00.799 --> 35:01.833
[ Grunts ]

35:03.535 --> 35:05.504
Michael.
How'd you find me?

35:05.571 --> 35:08.607
I know you.
You'd want to go down
guns blazing.

35:08.674 --> 35:11.310
- [ Vehicles Approaching ]
- Nice place for a last stand.

35:14.646 --> 35:16.448
- [ Chattering In Russian ]
- [ Vehicle Doors Closing ]

35:17.683 --> 35:18.850
It's not over.

35:18.917 --> 35:21.520
Karina sent for backup-- 12:00.

35:21.587 --> 35:23.389
- And your 6:00.
- Shall we?

35:26.958 --> 35:27.893
I thought you'd never ask.

35:40.672 --> 35:41.807
[ Groans ]

35:48.079 --> 35:49.448
I'm out.

35:59.858 --> 36:01.260
Get over here, Nicki.

36:02.628 --> 36:03.595
Reloading.

36:08.934 --> 36:10.469
Ready? Move!

36:15.006 --> 36:17.943
[ Men Shouting In Russian ]

36:21.012 --> 36:22.448
[ Gunfire Continues ]

36:40.432 --> 36:42.834
- [ Kevin ] What's, uh--
What's with the commandos?
- Get in the chopper.

36:42.901 --> 36:46.272
Yeah, I'm not going anywhere
until I know exactly
where that thing is going.

36:46.338 --> 36:49.741
Virginia, C.I.A. headquarters
in Langley, maybe
a quick stop in the Caribbean.

36:49.808 --> 36:51.943
Guantanamo's lovely
this time of year.

36:52.010 --> 36:54.346
Oh, my God.
It's okay. They'll cut
a deal with you.

36:54.413 --> 36:55.914
Later you can pawn
that ring and start anew.

36:55.981 --> 36:59.485
What about me, huh?
I'm not gonna get a deal.

36:59.551 --> 37:01.152
You think I'm getting
on that thing?

37:01.219 --> 37:02.588
There is no way!
[ Man ]
Weapon down!

37:02.654 --> 37:04.590
- Stand down.
- [ Man ]
Put the gun down!

37:04.656 --> 37:06.191
Fine. You want to
stay here?

37:06.258 --> 37:07.726
Good luck
with your Russian friends.

37:07.793 --> 37:10.729
After your daring escape,
don't expect a warm reception.

37:18.470 --> 37:21.340
- [ Man ] Let's go. Turn around.
- [ Man #2 ] Keep your hands
where we can see them.

37:21.407 --> 37:23.241
Okay, you know what?
I know my rights.

37:23.309 --> 37:25.076
You will never get
a word out of me!

37:25.143 --> 37:27.979
Yeah? Well,
they're gonna get
plenty out of me!

37:33.018 --> 37:34.586
Thank you, Michael.

37:34.653 --> 37:37.889
For what?
Quality time.

37:43.128 --> 37:45.731
[ Siren Blares ]
Okay, appreciate it.
Appreciate it. Thank you.

37:45.797 --> 37:48.667
Tavian said 6:00 p.m., right?
Any word?

37:48.734 --> 37:50.602
No. Haven't heard
from Mike either.

37:50.669 --> 37:53.705
He must still be flying back.
I can't believe he's gonna be
late to his own showdown.

37:53.772 --> 37:55.707
My buddies
at Homeland Security
just bought him some time.

37:55.774 --> 37:57.876
They came through, man--
by land, by sea and by air.

37:57.943 --> 37:59.578
Yeah. You must have called in
a lot of favors.

37:59.645 --> 38:02.914
Uh-- Yeah, that,
and I kind of told them I was
tracking a smuggled weapon...

38:02.981 --> 38:04.750
that may or may not be
leaking radioactive material.

38:04.816 --> 38:06.652
[ Chuckles ]
Oh! You went nuclear on them?

38:06.718 --> 38:08.320
Yeah,
I figured it wasn't time
to pull punches.

38:08.387 --> 38:09.721
It should buy us
at least four hours.

38:09.788 --> 38:11.723
Well, let's hope Mikey
gets here quick.

38:11.790 --> 38:13.892
Yeah, and Tavian
hasn't stood him up.
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]

38:15.427 --> 38:18.129
Hey, speak of the Tavian.
I'll make sure he's here.
I'll be back.

38:18.196 --> 38:19.331
[ Beeps ]
Yeah?

38:20.332 --> 38:21.900
I thought we had
an agreement.

38:21.967 --> 38:23.469
Where is Michael Westen?

38:23.535 --> 38:25.504
Well, he's at
Brickell Key Park,
just like you wanted.

38:25.571 --> 38:27.272
He's not there.
You're lying.

38:27.339 --> 38:29.641
What? Me lie? No, he's there.
Check again. It's a big place.

38:29.708 --> 38:31.009
Maybe you haven't
looked hard enough.

38:31.076 --> 38:34.680
I'm on Brickell Key, staring at
the meeting point. No Michael.

38:34.746 --> 38:37.082
Well, I guess he just
must be running late.

38:37.148 --> 38:39.485
You know,
I'm not a patient man.

38:39.551 --> 38:42.187
This is a one-time offer.
We're done.

38:42.253 --> 38:45.691
Yeah, uh, before you skedaddle,
you might want to take a look
at the water.

38:45.757 --> 38:48.159
You see those police
patrol boats?

38:48.226 --> 38:50.896
They're not letting any boats
in or out for the next
two or three hours.

38:50.962 --> 38:53.231
We've also locked down
the airspace.

38:53.298 --> 38:58.604
Oh, and in case you were
planning a road trip, I wouldn't
exactly pack your bags.

38:58.670 --> 39:01.172
You'll get your meet with Mike,
but you're gonna have to wait.

39:01.239 --> 39:02.641
[ Beeps ]

39:02.708 --> 39:04.843
Well, we got the tiger
by the tail.

39:04.910 --> 39:07.579
Yeah, let's hope it doesn't
rip Mike's head off
when he gets here.

39:10.849 --> 39:13.251
You know,
I've been thinking.

39:13.318 --> 39:15.587
The world
is a dangerous place.

39:15.654 --> 39:20.692
I bet there are lots of
wanted types laying low
in Spain, Italy, France.

39:20.759 --> 39:22.961
Are you volunteering
for more extraction jobs?

39:23.862 --> 39:25.564
Paris is lovely
in the spring.

39:29.501 --> 39:31.737
I guess I won't be
needing this anymore.

39:33.705 --> 39:34.606
Let me.

39:38.810 --> 39:41.146
Mr. Jenson,
it was nice being
married to you.

39:42.013 --> 39:43.214
You too, Mrs. Jenson.

39:43.281 --> 39:46.017
Maybe I'll hang on to this.
Never know when I'll need it.

39:47.285 --> 39:48.787
For another job.

39:51.289 --> 39:54.359
Well, next time I'm your wife,
I prefer an Asscher-cut diamond.

39:54.426 --> 39:55.694
Good to know.

40:02.668 --> 40:04.603
Well, I guess
the honeymoon's over.

40:06.337 --> 40:08.674
I'm, uh-- I'm gonna
go to the tailor.

40:08.740 --> 40:11.309
Maybe he can turn my ripped gown
into a mini-dress.

40:11.376 --> 40:14.880
I'm gonna check in
with Sam and Jesse
about the Tavian situation.

40:16.515 --> 40:18.750
Happy hunting.

40:18.817 --> 40:21.086
Maybe later, when you're done,
we could do
a little reconnecting.

40:26.858 --> 40:28.426
Agent Pearce?

40:29.294 --> 40:30.629
Make yourself at home.

40:30.696 --> 40:32.931
Sorry.
I let myself in.

40:32.998 --> 40:34.466
But I've got something
that couldn't wait.

40:34.533 --> 40:36.101
[ Sighs ]

40:36.167 --> 40:38.436
I think I have a break
in Max's murder case.

40:38.504 --> 40:41.406
Since you worked
so hard on this, I thought you
should be the first to know.

40:41.473 --> 40:44.476
- You made it through
all the files I gave you?
- Not yet.

40:44.543 --> 40:49.715
Remember a few weeks ago,
I said we couldn't find anything
on the traffic cams?

40:49.781 --> 40:52.584
Our killer was smart enough
to avoid all of them,

40:52.651 --> 40:55.220
which means
at some point,

40:55.286 --> 40:58.657
he'd have to
turn down... here.

40:58.724 --> 41:02.060
Now, Third Street has a law firm
with security cameras
on the entrance...

41:02.127 --> 41:03.562
and lots of glass walls,

41:03.629 --> 41:06.197
which means you can see
the passing cars.

41:08.199 --> 41:11.169
I pulled the footage
from after Max was shot.

41:11.236 --> 41:14.439
Image wasn't great,
but N.S.A. helped me
clean it up.

41:14.506 --> 41:16.041
Check it out.

41:16.107 --> 41:17.075
[ Beeping ]

41:25.817 --> 41:28.186
I can explain.
The man who killed Max--

41:30.556 --> 41:32.090
It was you.

41:32.157 --> 41:33.692
You lied to me.

41:33.759 --> 41:35.527
You were there.
You killed him!

41:35.594 --> 41:38.329
No, Pearce. No.

41:38.396 --> 41:42.634
I was framed, and I knew I would
go down for this if I didn't
find the guy who did it.

41:44.870 --> 41:46.137
Now, I couldn't trust you
back then.

41:46.204 --> 41:48.607
- [ Scoffs ]
- Listen to me. I found him.

41:48.674 --> 41:50.942
Stop lying.

41:52.978 --> 41:55.413
He's Romanian.
His name is Tavian.

41:55.480 --> 41:57.616
Sam and Jesse are
tracking him right now.

41:57.683 --> 41:59.184
Just let me make
one phone ca--

42:00.919 --> 42:03.454
- Don't even think about it.
- You are making a mistake!

42:03.521 --> 42:05.223
My mistake was trusting you.

42:08.594 --> 42:11.029
Let's go. Now!
